          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-09 23:57:51" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to think, with the purpose of planning or deciding on a course of action</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to purpose</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to plan</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to intend</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages there are two quite distinct sets of terms for planning depending upon the purpose involved in such planning. If the planning is constructive, either for oneself or someone else, one set of terms is likely to be used, while if the planning is harmful (usually against someone else), another set of terms would be used.|This meaning is also found as a variant reading: Οἱ δὲ ἀκούσαντες διεπρίοντο καὶ ἐβούλοντο ἀνελεῖν αὐτούς ‘but when they heard this they were furious, for they were planning to put them to death’ {S:04400503300012} (apparatus).</Comments>
